I have a question I built some serverless functions on <https://6326255.hs-sites.com/> and I'm now taking the functionality live to this url: <https://www.oxyensure.com/>. When I try to view my one GET serverless functions in the browser I get this error:  This site canâ€™t be reached. <http://Oxyensure.com|Oxyensure.com> unexpectedly closed the connection. When I try to send formData to this endpoint I get this response: HTTP ERROR 415 Problem accessing /cms/v3/function-executor/execute/by-path/update-plan. Reason: Unsupported Media Type.

I'm not sure if something in my setup is wrong.

Here's my JS for sending the formData to one of my endpoint. It works on the <https://6326255.hs-sites.com/>.

```$("#plan-selected-form").on('submit', function(e, data){
      e.preventDefault();

      var formData = [];
      formData[0]= ($("#plan-selected-form input[name='plan-id']").val()+1);

      updatePlan(formData);
      console.log(formData)
    });

    function updatePlan(data){
      console.log(data);

      $.post('/_hcms/api/update-plan', JSON.stringify(data), function(result, status){
        $("#delivery-info-plan plan").html(result);
        window.location.href = 'checkout-dev';
      }, 'html');

    }```
